{
  "stem": "15082.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We had a total of [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] four shuls-- four houses of worship.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The main house was the shul, which was about 500 feet from the back of our house.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That shul was the shul that my grandfather, Israel Chartan, as long as I can remember, all these years he was the president.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the other shul was called the [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] shul.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They call it a [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], which was a-- because of the [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH] rabbi, which was very famous, he used to come and stay there.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The other was the [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], which was about a half a block away from the main shul.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the fourth one was the-- called the-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] the [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], which was another rabbi, after another rabbi.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And in these towns, almost-- quite often, these rabbis would travel through, and spend the Shabbat in the town.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was also very outstanding with me, because my grandfather would bring me to [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], which was Friday night, and Saturday services.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And then also when you do the [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], which was always outstanding in my mind.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the people enjoyed themselves, and partaking with the rabbi, and studying.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I was a kid.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So it was a big impression to watch him.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Very close relationship, because he lived so close.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My other grandfather, [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], lived about seven miles away.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I used to see him a lot, but not as often as living in the same house.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I remember a lot of Saturdays when the weather was nice, we would walk those seven kilometers after services and Shabbos to go to visit my grandfather.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then at night, we'd be driven home by horse and buggy, like we drove back to our hometown.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
